b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe48204.htm)  [Next](sbe48206.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n36\\. And because all the attributes are proved (to be present in Brahman).\n\nAs all those attributes required to constitute causality which have been or\nwill be shown to be absent in the Pradhana, the atoms, and so on, can be shown\nto be present in Brahman, it remains a settled conclusion that Brahman only is\nthe cause of the world. Here terminates the adhikara _n_ a of 'that which has\nthe nature of depending on a motive.'\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: Second Pada: 1. Not that which is inferred, on account of the\nimpossibility of construction, and on account of activity](sbe48206.htm)\n\n"